description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting and opportunity has arisen for a dynamic and enthusiastic senior nurse, passionate about education to join the corporate nurse education team as a Practice Development Nurse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Practice Development Nurse Role is essential in influencing learning and the professional development of our nursing staff by providing support and educational input to nurses of all levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a nurse who has significant clinical experience within an acute hospital environment. Previous experience within a clinical education role is desirable. This role is a great opportunity for a nurse with an education focus to develop their skills within a supportive corporate nurse education team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This successful candidate will spend time teaching and supporting staff in clinical areas as well as developing and leading on education programmes delivered at an organisation level. The individual will be an advocate of our trust values and ensure equal opportunities to all.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be taking place week commencing 30th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is offered as a full time position 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contac please contcat:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tracy Webb, Head of Nursing/Midwifery for Workforce, Education &amp; Development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: tracy.webb4@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
